<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/three-question-test/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Constraint docs" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/three-question-test/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/three-question-test> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "Quick assessment before running the full five constraints. All three must hold: (1) Multi-party data — multiple independent parties share a common data set. (2) Institutional anchor — an institution defines what is valid but does not want to run infrastructure. (3) Verifiable history — historical integrity matters, parties must not rewrite past records. If only 1-2 hold, a traditional database suffices." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/three-question-test> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#constraints> .
