<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/three-question-test> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/isPartOf> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/three-question-test> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/kinds#constraint> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/three-question-test> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#Node> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/thesis> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#externalLink> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/thesis/link/0> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/thesis/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://lambdasistemi.github.io/cardano-for-regulators/thesis/"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/thesis/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Full text" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/thesis/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/thesis> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "The economic and philosophical foundation. Web3 is expensive because it is honest — the cost buys guarantees Web2 cannot provide. Users will not pay per action, so a sponsor must absorb the cost. Regulation is the forcing function that compels businesses to need blockchain guarantees, making sponsorship the cheapest way to comply." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/thesis> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#foundation> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/thesis> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "The Thesis" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/thesis> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#nodeId> "thesis" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/thesis> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/isPartOf> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/thesis> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/kinds#concept> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/thesis> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#Node> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-minimisation> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#externalLink> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-minimisation/link/0> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-minimisation/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://gdpr-info.eu/art-5-gdpr/"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-minimisation/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "GDPR Art 5" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-minimisation/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-minimisation> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "GDPR requires collecting only what is necessary (Art 5(1)(c)). Blockchain replicates all data to every full node. Resolution: only hashes on-chain — minimal by design. The actual data behind the leaves is verified off-chain by the operator. The on-chain footprint per compliance record is a single hash, which is the minimum required to prove integrity." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-minimisation> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#tensions> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-minimisation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Data Minimisation vs Replication" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-minimisation> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#nodeId> "tension-minimisation" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-minimisation> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/isPartOf> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-minimisation> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/kinds#risk> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-minimisation> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#Node> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-erasure> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#externalLink> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-erasure/link/0> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-erasure/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://gdpr-info.eu/art-17-gdpr/"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-erasure/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "GDPR Art 17" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-erasure/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-erasure> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "The most cited GDPR-blockchain conflict. Art 17 grants the right to erasure — but blockchain data cannot be deleted. Resolution: no personal data on-chain. Compliance records are not subject to erasure — they are the controller's proof of accountability. The right to erasure applies to the off-chain personal data, which remains under the controller's custody." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-erasure> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#tensions> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-erasure> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Immutability vs Erasure" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-erasure> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#nodeId> "tension-erasure" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-erasure> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/isPartOf> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-erasure> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/kinds#risk> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-erasure> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#Node> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-controller-designation> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#externalLink> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-controller-designation/link/0> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-controller-designation/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://www.cnil.fr/en/blockchain-and-gdpr-solutions-responsible-use-blockchain-context-personal-data"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-controller-designation/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "CNIL blockchain guidance" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-controller-designation/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-controller-designation> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "GDPR requires identifiable controllers and processors. Public blockchains have no central controller. Resolution: the data controller is the operator of their own trie — clearly identifiable. The identity provider, SA, and chain validators are not controllers of the compliance data. CNIL's 2018 guidance supports this: smart contract deployers who determine purposes and means are controllers." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-controller-designation> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#tensions> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-controller-designation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Controller Designation" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-controller-designation> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#nodeId> "tension-controller-designation" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-controller-designation> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/isPartOf> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-controller-designation> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/kinds#risk> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/tension-controller-designation> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#Node> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/temporal-integrity> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#externalLink> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/temporal-integrity/link/0> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/temporal-integrity/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://lambdasistemi.github.io/cardano-for-regulators/thesis/#time-as-the-neutral-witness"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/temporal-integrity/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Thesis section" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/temporal-integrity/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/temporal-integrity> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "The blockchain provides time certificates that neither party produced. When data is included in a block, it receives a temporal proof that is a consequence of consensus, not of anyone's claim. This is critical for regulations with deadlines — the 72-hour breach notification, the 1-month rights response — where self-reported timestamps are not neutral." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/temporal-integrity> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#foundation> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/temporal-integrity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Temporal Integrity" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/temporal-integrity> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#nodeId> "temporal-integrity" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/temporal-integrity> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/isPartOf> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/temporal-integrity> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/kinds#concept> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/temporal-integrity> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#Node> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/sponsor-pays> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#externalLink> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/sponsor-pays/link/0> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/sponsor-pays/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://lambdasistemi.github.io/cardano-for-regulators/thesis/#the-sponsor-pays"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/sponsor-pays/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Thesis section" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/sponsor-pays/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/sponsor-pays> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "The entity that benefits from on-chain guarantees pays for them — not the user. In regulated industries, the obligated party (manufacturer, importer, controller) already pays for compliance infrastructure. Sponsoring blockchain transactions is a different line item, potentially cheaper than proprietary audit systems or manual inspections." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/sponsor-pays> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#foundation> .
