<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/relay-state-machine/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://lambdasistemi.github.io/cardano-for-regulators/framework/patterns/#relay-state-machine"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/relay-state-machine/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Pattern docs" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/relay-state-machine/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/relay-state-machine> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "Multiple actors act in sequence, each contributing their part. The regulation defines the ordering. Each actor can only act when it is their turn. Timeout or escalation if an actor misses the deadline. The trie serializes access naturally — no contention because the regulation already requires sequential processing." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/relay-state-machine> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#protocols> .
