<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/regulator/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://lambdasistemi.github.io/cardano-for-regulators/framework/schema/#what-the-regulator-produces"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/regulator/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Schema: what the regulator produces" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/regulator/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/regulator> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "The institution that defines the rules. Maintains the regulation trie (actor qualifications, operator standing), publishes the smart contract encoding the regulation, and defines the beacon minting policy. Does not run infrastructure or manage identities. Audits that operators use the correct smart contract. Cannot retroactively revise its own history — the chain makes the regulator answerable." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/regulator> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#schema> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/regulator> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Regulator" .
