<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/regulator> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/isPartOf> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/regulator> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/kinds#party> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/regulator> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#Node> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/regulation-trie> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#externalLink> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/regulation-trie/link/0> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/regulation-trie/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://lambdasistemi.github.io/cardano-for-regulators/framework/schema/#what-the-regulator-produces"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/regulation-trie/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Schema section" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/regulation-trie/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/regulation-trie> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "A Merkle Patricia Trie maintained by the regulator. Serves two purposes: actor qualifications (process-specific credentials like licensed carrier, authorized dispatcher) and operator standing (compliance scores, flags, warnings). The standing is the regulator's judgment — it fuses on-chain and off-chain inputs and cannot be independently recomputed." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/regulation-trie> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#schema> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/regulation-trie> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Regulation Trie" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/regulation-trie> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#nodeId> "regulation-trie" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/regulation-trie> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/isPartOf> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/regulation-trie> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/kinds#artifact> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/regulation-trie> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#Node> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/process-trie> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#externalLink> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/process-trie/link/0> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/process-trie/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://lambdasistemi.github.io/cardano-for-regulators/framework/schema/#what-the-operator-does"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/process-trie/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Schema section" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/process-trie/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/process-trie> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "A Merkle Patricia Trie maintained by each operator. Contains items, processes, and state — one UTxO per operator regardless of item count. Governed by the regulator's smart contract. The operator is the sole writer, eliminating contention. Items are leaves; updates recompute the root hash." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/process-trie> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#schema> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/process-trie> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Process Trie" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/process-trie> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#nodeId> "process-trie" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/process-trie> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/isPartOf> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/process-trie> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/kinds#artifact> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/process-trie> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#Node> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/process-mode> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#externalLink> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/process-mode/link/0> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/process-mode/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://lambdasistemi.github.io/cardano-for-regulators/framework/schema/#process-mode"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/process-mode/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Schema section" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/process-mode/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/process-mode> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "No physical object — just a logical process advancing through stages. A permit application, a certification workflow, a supply chain declaration, or a GDPR compliance record. The signing function lives on a server. Trust comes from protocol: double signature proves the right actor performed the right action, commitment proves timeliness, smart contract proves correctness." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/process-mode> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#modes> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/process-mode> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Process Mode" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/process-mode> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#nodeId> "process-mode" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/process-mode> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/isPartOf> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/process-mode> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/kinds#concept> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/process-mode> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#Node> .
