<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/physical-mode/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://lambdasistemi.github.io/cardano-for-regulators/framework/schema/#physical-mode"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/physical-mode/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Schema section" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/physical-mode/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/physical-mode> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "The object carries its own identity and attests its own state. A battery with a sensor and secure element signs its state of health. The data comes from the thing itself — a physical measurement. Trust comes from hardware: the sensor measured reality, the secure element signed it, the chain anchored it. Strictly stronger than process mode." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/physical-mode> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#modes> .
