<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/informed-consent/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://lambdasistemi.github.io/cardano-for-regulators/thesis/#informed-consent-by-construction"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/informed-consent/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Thesis section" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/informed-consent/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/informed-consent> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "The beacon turns the blockchain into a disclosure channel. The user signs over the beacon — which includes the regulator's assessment of the operator — as part of their payload. This is cryptographic proof of awareness. The user cannot claim ignorance when the chain shows they signed over the disclosure. Consent enforced by protocol, not by policy." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/informed-consent> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#foundation> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/informed-consent> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Informed Consent by Construction" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/informed-consent> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#nodeId> "informed-consent" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/informed-consent> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/isPartOf> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/informed-consent> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/kinds#concept> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/informed-consent> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#Node> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/identity-trie> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#externalLink> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/identity-trie/link/0> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/identity-trie/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://lambdasistemi.github.io/cardano-for-regulators/framework/schema/#what-the-identity-provider-does"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/identity-trie/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Schema section" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/identity-trie/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/identity-trie> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "A Merkle Patricia Trie maintained by the identity provider. Contains attested actor public keys. Used as a reference input by the smart contract — read-only from the operator's perspective. Prevents the operator from inventing fake actors. The validator checks membership at every transaction." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/identity-trie> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#schema> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/identity-trie> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Identity Trie" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/identity-trie> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#nodeId> "identity-trie" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/identity-trie> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/isPartOf> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/identity-trie> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/kinds#artifact> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/identity-trie> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#Node> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/identity-provider> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#externalLink> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/identity-provider/link/0> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/identity-provider/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://lambdasistemi.github.io/cardano-for-regulators/framework/schema/#what-the-identity-provider-does"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/identity-provider/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Schema section" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/identity-provider/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/identity-provider> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "Maintains a Merkle Patricia Trie of verified real-world entities. Each verified entity gets a leaf with their attested public key. The same identity trie can serve multiple regulators and multiple regulations. Prevents the operator from faking users — every actor in a regulated process must have a key in the trusted identity trie." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/identity-provider> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#schema> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/identity-provider> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Identity Provider" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/identity-provider> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#nodeId> "identity-provider" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/identity-provider> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/isPartOf> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/identity-provider> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/kinds#party> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/identity-provider> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#Node> .
