<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/gdpr-breach-notification/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://gdpr-info.eu/art-33-gdpr/"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/gdpr-breach-notification/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "GDPR Art 33" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/gdpr-breach-notification/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/gdpr-breach-notification> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "Controller must notify the supervisory authority within 72 hours of becoming aware of a personal data breach (Art 33). The flagship on-chain use case. Currently self-reported with no neutral witness. Commitment-then-submit turns this into a verifiable on-chain fact. Absence of a timely commitment, when a breach becomes known through other channels, is evidence of non-compliance." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/gdpr-breach-notification> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#gdpr> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/gdpr-breach-notification> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Breach Notification (72h)" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/gdpr-breach-notification> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#nodeId> "gdpr-breach-notification" .
