<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/double-signature> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#externalLink> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/double-signature/link/0> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/double-signature/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://lambdasistemi.github.io/cardano-for-regulators/framework/schema/#the-double-signature"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/double-signature/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Schema section" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/double-signature/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/double-signature> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "Every state transition requires two signatures. The process signature proves this specific process produced this data at this time (authentication). The actor signature proves the authorized party requests this transition (authorization). Neither alone is sufficient — together they prove an authorized, attested, qualified actor interacted with a specific process." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/double-signature> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#protocols> .
