<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-sequential-access/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Constraint docs" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-sequential-access/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-sequential-access> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "Writes to the shared state must be naturally serialized — no concurrent contention. Either a single operator writes (most common), or multiple actors relay in sequence where the regulation defines the ordering. The MPT stored in a single UTxO is inherently sequential: only one transaction can consume and recreate it per block." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-sequential-access> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#constraints> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-sequential-access> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Sequential Access" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-sequential-access> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#nodeId> "constraint-sequential-access" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-sequential-access> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/isPartOf> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-sequential-access> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/kinds#constraint> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-sequential-access> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#Node> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-liveness> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#externalLink> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-liveness/link/0> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-liveness/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://lambdasistemi.github.io/cardano-for-regulators/framework/constraints/#3-liveness"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-liveness/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Constraint docs" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-liveness/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-liveness> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "The regulation must provide deadlines and penalties that incentivize continued participation. If one actor in a relay stops, the chain stalls. External liveness comes from the legal system (fines, market withdrawal, license loss). Protocol escalation adds on-chain mechanisms: slot-based timeouts, bond/deposit slashing, fallback operators." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-liveness> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#constraints> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-liveness> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Liveness" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-liveness> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#nodeId> "constraint-liveness" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-liveness> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/isPartOf> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-liveness> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/kinds#constraint> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-liveness> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#Node> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-identity-delegation> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#externalLink> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-identity-delegation/link/0> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-identity-delegation/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://lambdasistemi.github.io/cardano-for-regulators/framework/constraints/#5-identity-delegation"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-identity-delegation/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Constraint docs" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-identity-delegation/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-identity-delegation> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "Actors who will never have wallets must make meaningful on-chain state transitions through cryptographic proxies. A secure element in a product, an institutional smart card, a mobile credential, or a QR challenge. The proxy bridges the physical world to the chain: proving who, what, and when without blockchain knowledge." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-identity-delegation> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#constraints> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-identity-delegation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Identity Delegation" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-identity-delegation> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#nodeId> "constraint-identity-delegation" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-identity-delegation> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/isPartOf> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-identity-delegation> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/kinds#constraint> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-identity-delegation> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#Node> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-fee-alignment> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#externalLink> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-fee-alignment/link/0> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-fee-alignment/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://lambdasistemi.github.io/cardano-for-regulators/framework/constraints/#4-fee-alignment"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-fee-alignment/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Constraint docs" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-fee-alignment/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-fee-alignment> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "There must be an actor who benefits enough from on-chain compliance to pay — the sponsor. Users do not pay. The regulation mandates the obligated party, and the cost per operation is negligible at scale. Happy path: operator pays willingly. Sad path: user has leverage via escrow, bond, or direct submission." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-fee-alignment> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#constraints> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-fee-alignment> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Fee Alignment" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-fee-alignment> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#nodeId> "constraint-fee-alignment" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-fee-alignment> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/isPartOf> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-fee-alignment> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/kinds#constraint> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-fee-alignment> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#Node> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-data-cadence> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#externalLink> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-data-cadence/link/0> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-data-cadence/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://lambdasistemi.github.io/cardano-for-regulators/framework/constraints/#1-data-cadence"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-data-cadence/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Constraint docs" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-data-cadence/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-data-cadence> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "The regulation's data update rhythm must be compatible with L1 settlement. Periodic reporting, event-driven updates, and batch submissions all fit. Real-time sensor telemetry at 100ms intervals does not. The MPT-per-operator pattern means each operator submits one transaction per batch regardless of how many items were updated." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-data-cadence> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#constraints> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-data-cadence> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Data Cadence" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-data-cadence> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#nodeId> "constraint-data-cadence" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-data-cadence> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/isPartOf> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-data-cadence> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/kinds#constraint> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/constraint-data-cadence> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#Node> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/commitment-protocol> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#externalLink> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/commitment-protocol/link/0> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/commitment-protocol/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://lambdasistemi.github.io/cardano-for-regulators/framework/patterns/#commitment-then-submit"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/commitment-protocol/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Pattern docs" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/commitment-protocol/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/commitment-protocol> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "Proves that an action occurred within a specific time window. The operator creates a commitment in a trie leaf with validFrom and validUntil slots. The user's reading or response clears the commitment. Single-use (prevents replay), slot-bounded (validator checks the window), and requires no off-chain timestamp trust. The core mechanism for GDPR's 72h breach notification and 1-month rights response." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/commitment-protocol> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#protocols> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/commitment-protocol> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Commitment-then-Submit" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/commitment-protocol> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#nodeId> "commitment-protocol" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/commitment-protocol> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/isPartOf> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/commitment-protocol> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/kinds#protocol> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/commitment-protocol> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#Node> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/bright-line> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#externalLink> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/bright-line/link/1> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/bright-line/link/1> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://www.cnil.fr/en/blockchain-and-gdpr-solutions-responsible-use-blockchain-context-personal-data"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/bright-line/link/1> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "CNIL blockchain guidance" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/bright-line/link/1> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/bright-line> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#externalLink> <https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/bright-line/link/0> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/bright-line/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://gdpr-info.eu/recitals/no-26/"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/bright-line/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "GDPR Recital 26" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/bright-line/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/bright-line> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "The architectural principle that resolves every GDPR-blockchain tension: personal data off-chain, compliance evidence on-chain. No names, identifiers, health data, location, or behavioural profiles ever touch the chain — not even encrypted. The chain stores hashes of compliance records. Under Recital 26's 'means reasonably likely' test, properly segregated hashes are not personal data." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/bright-line> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#gdpr> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/bright-line> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "The Bright Line" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/bright-line> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#nodeId> "bright-line" .
