<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/battery-regulation/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://lambdasistemi.github.io/cardano-for-regulators/cases/battery-regulation/"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/battery-regulation/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Case study" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/battery-regulation/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/battery-regulation> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "The reference case — (EU) 2023/1542 on batteries and waste batteries. All five constraints pass. Physical mode with NFC secure element signing SoH readings. MPT-per-operator with ~200 manufacturers, ~5M batteries/year. Commitment-then-submit for authenticated readings. Hardware cost $1.91 per module at volume. Annual on-chain cost ~$1,800-3,600 for the entire market." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/battery-regulation> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#cases> .
