<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/baton-pattern/link/0> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#url> "https://lambdasistemi.github.io/cardano-for-regulators/framework/schema/#the-baton-pattern"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/baton-pattern/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Schema section" .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/baton-pattern/link/0> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#ExternalLink> .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/baton-pattern> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#description> "Authorization to act on a process travels as a baton through the real world. The first tap makes Actor A the holder. Actor A's final submission includes Actor B's pubkey, atomically transferring the baton. No gap where nobody holds authorization — the transfer is part of the state transition. No user registration, no identity database, no login." .
<https://github.com/lambdasistemi/cardano-for-regulators/rdf/node/baton-pattern> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/terms#group> <https://lambdasistemi.github.io/graph-browser/vocab/groups#protocols> .
